  <title translate="true">Backlash</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Backlash</keyword>
    <keyword translate="true">Lash</keyword>
    <keyword translate="true">Lost-motion</keyword>
    <keyword translate="true">Play</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para><table styleclass="MotionPupup" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is in a mechanical system when there is a physical gap between two elements. It is detrimental to the performance of the mechanism. When </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is traversed, (the contact moves across the gap), the elements travel with different velocities and there is an </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Impact" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">impact</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Backlash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> should be avoided. However, in special circumstances, it can reduce residual vibration!</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:normal; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Other names</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Lash</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> (especially with respect to valve settings of auto-engines), </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Play</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
